<h3>Learn to Make a Contribution to your Business or Office</h3>
<p>The Applied Associates in Administrative Assistant/Office Manager is designed to give students the skills necessary to immediately make a difference in the workplace. Students will develop office skills including: teamwork, information processing, communication, records management, customer service ethics, and more. Students will also learn how to use spreadsheets and databases to solve business problems, as well as the basic accounting processes businesses use.</p>
<p><strong>Students will participate in the following areas of study:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>General Accounting</li>
<li>Office Procedures</li>
<li>Applications for Business (spreadsheets, database applications, etc.)</li>
<li>Human Resource Management</li>
</ul>
<h3>Degree Overview</h3>
<p><strong> </strong>The AAS Administrative Assistant degree can be taken entirely online. Students must complete 17 credits of required&nbsp;<a href="http://www.byui.edu/Documents/catalog/2013-2014/Foundations.pdf">Foundations courses</a> and 36 credits of major courses (listed below) plus 7 elective credits for a total of 60 credits. Minors or concentrations in the Business Department are also available. Review the course list below or check the <a href="http://www.byui.edu/Documents/catalog/2012-2013/Business%20Management.pdf">University Catalog</a> for specific degree requirements. Check <a href="x33948.xml">course availability</a> and offerings or contact us today at <span class="skype_c2c_print_container">(208) 496-1800</span><span class="skype_c2c_container" dir="ltr" onmouseout="SkypeClick2Call.MenuInjectionHandler.hideMenu(event)" onmouseover="SkypeClick2Call.MenuInjectionHandler.showMenu(this, event)"><span class="skype_c2c_highlighting_inactive_common" dir="ltr"><span class="skype_c2c_textarea_span"><img class="skype_c2c_logo_img" src="resource://skype_ff_extension-at-jetpack/skype_ff_extension/data/call_skype_logo.png" /><span class="skype_c2c_text_span">(208) 496-1800</span><span class="skype_c2c_free_text_span"></span></span></span></span>.</p>
